OL,4,Cenergy 'just transition' ` report
OL,6,FUnderlining the scale of the
OL,7,Fchallenge, he said that in order for
OL,8,Fthe workforce to be sustained at
OL,9,Fcurrent levels of just over 150,000 in
OL,10,F2030, the installation of new offshore
OL,11,Fturbines would need to increase to
OL,12,Froughly one per day.
OL,14,FIn addition, the UK would need to
OL,15,Fcontinue extracting around 500,000
OL,16,Fbarrels of oil equivalent per day.
OL,18,FThe total installed capacity of
OL,19,Foffshore wind generation would need to
OL,20,Fincrease to around 40GW, up from 15GW
OL,21,Fat the end of 2023.
